Installs INI file with object LOD pointing toward LOD16. This is the default option.#13;


USE THIS OPTION UNLESS YOU UNDERSTAND THE ALTERNATIVE.#13;


See instructions on the mod page.#13;


This is for users who do NOT use DynDOLOD Level32=1.

IF YOU DO NOT USE DYNDOLOD YOU MUST USE THIS FILE. 

If you use DynDOLOD, and you do NOT change Level32=1 in the INI file, you MUST use this file.

Installs INI file with object LOD pointing toward LOD32. This is for users who use DynDOLOD Level32=1.#13;


You MUST follow the instructions on the mod page for this to work correctly! Failure to do so will cause LOD to be rendered incorrectly.#13;


DO NOT USE THIS UNLESS YOU KNOW WHAT YOU ARE DOING.
